# Sequence Diagram - OAuth 2.0 Authentication

## Complete Authentication Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant C as Client (App)
    participant AS as Auth Server
    participant RS as Resource Server
    participant DB as Database

    Note over U,DB: OAuth 2.0 login start

    U->>C: Click "Log In"
    C->>AS: Redirect to /auth/authorize
    Note right of AS: client_id, redirect_uri, scope

    AS->>U: Show login form
    U->>AS: Enter credentials
    AS->>DB: Validate user
    DB-->>AS: Valid user

    AS->>U: Show consent page
    U->>AS: Authorize application

    AS->>C: Redirect with authorization code
    Note right of AS: ?code=auth_code&state=xyz

    C->>AS: POST /token with code
    Note right of C: client_id, client_secret, code

    AS->>AS: Validate code and client
    AS->>AS: Generate access_token and refresh_token
    AS-->>C: Return tokens

    Note over U,DB: Access to protected resources

    U->>C: Request profile data
    C->>RS: GET /api/profile
    Note right of C: Authorization: Bearer {access_token}

    RS->>AS: Validate access_token
    AS-->>RS: Valid token + scopes

    RS->>DB: Query user data
    DB-->>RS: Profile data
    RS-->>C: Return profile data
    C-->>U: Show profile information

    Note over U,DB: Token renewal

    C->>AS: POST /token/refresh
    Note right of C: refresh_token + client credentials
    AS->>AS: Validate refresh_token
    AS-->>C: New access_token
```

