# Cloud Infrastructure Diagram

## AWS High-Availability Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Public Internet"
        USERS[👥 Users]
        CDN[CloudFront CDN]
    end

    subgraph "AWS Region - us-east-1"
        subgraph "Availability Zone A"
            subgraph "Public Subnet A"
                ALB[Application Load Balancer]
                NAT_A[NAT Gateway A]
            end

            subgraph "Private Subnet A"
                EC2_A1[EC2 Instance A1]
                EC2_A2[EC2 Instance A2]
                RDS_A[RDS Primary]
            end
        end

        subgraph "Availability Zone B"
            subgraph "Public Subnet B"
                NAT_B[NAT Gateway B]
            end

            subgraph "Private Subnet B"
                EC2_B1[EC2 Instance B1]
                EC2_B2[EC2 Instance B2]
                RDS_B[RDS Standby]
            end
        end

        subgraph "Storage & Services"
            S3[S3 Bucket]
            ELASTICACHE[ElastiCache Redis]
            SQS[SQS Queue]
            SNS[SNS Topics]
        end
    end

    subgraph "Monitoring & Security"
        CLOUDWATCH[CloudWatch]
        IAM[IAM Roles & Policies]
        VPC[VPC Security Groups]
        SECRETS[Secrets Manager]
    end

    USERS --> CDN
    CDN --> ALB
    ALB --> EC2_A1
    ALB --> EC2_A2
    ALB --> EC2_B1
    ALB --> EC2_B2

    EC2_A1 --> RDS_A
    EC2_A2 --> RDS_A
    EC2_B1 --> RDS_A
    EC2_B2 --> RDS_A

    RDS_A -.->|Replication| RDS_B

    EC2_A1 --> ELASTICACHE
    EC2_A2 --> ELASTICACHE
    EC2_B1 --> ELASTICACHE
    EC2_B2 --> ELASTICACHE

    EC2_A1 --> S3
    EC2_A2 --> S3
    EC2_B1 --> S3
    EC2_B2 --> S3

    EC2_A1 --> SQS
    EC2_A2 --> SQS
    EC2_B1 --> SQS
    EC2_B2 --> SQS

    SQS --> SNS

    EC2_A1 --> NAT_A
    EC2_A2 --> NAT_A
    EC2_B1 --> NAT_B
    EC2_B2 --> NAT_B

    CLOUDWATCH -.-> EC2_A1
    CLOUDWATCH -.-> EC2_A2
    CLOUDWATCH -.-> EC2_B1
    CLOUDWATCH -.-> EC2_B2
    CLOUDWATCH -.-> RDS_A
    CLOUDWATCH -.-> RDS_B
```

